{"title_page": "Zoran Simovi\u0107", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Zoran Simovi\u0107\n| image          = \n| fullname       = Zoran Simovi\u0107\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1954|11|02|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Mojkovac]], [[Federal People's Republic of Yugoslavia|FPR Yugoslavia]]\n| height         = 1.86 m\n| position       = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub    = \n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = [[FK Obili\u0107evo Kru\u0161evac|Obili\u0107evo Kru\u0161evac]]\n| youthyears2    = \n| youthclubs2    = [[FK Napredak Kru\u0161evac|Napredak Kru\u0161evac]]\n| years1         = 1975\u20131980\n| clubs1         = [[FK Napredak Kru\u0161evac|Napredak Kru\u0161evac]]\n| caps1          = 108\n| goals1         = 1\n| years2         = 1980\u20131984\n| clubs2         = [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]]\n| caps2          = 84\n| goals2         = 0\n| years3         = 1984\u20131990\n| clubs3         = [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]]\n| caps3          = 192\n| goals3         = 1\n| totalcaps      = 384\n| totalgoals     = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 1983\u20131984\n| nationalteam1  = [[Yugoslavia national football team|Yugoslavia]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 10\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Zoran Simovi\u0107''' ([[Serbian Cyrillic alphabet|Cyrillic]]: \u0417\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043d \u0421\u0438\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0438\u045b; born 2 November 1954) is a former [[Yugoslavia|Yugoslav]] and [[Montenegro|Montenegrin]] [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.reprezentacija.rs/simovic-zoran/ | title=Simovi\u0107 Zoran | language=Serbian | publisher=reprezentacija.rs | access-date=28 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nSimovi\u0107 was named the [[Yugoslav Footballer of the Year]] in 1983. He also won the [[Milliyet Sports Awards|Turkish Footballer of the Year]] award for three consecutive years (1985, 1986, and 1987).\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Mojkovac]], [[People's Republic of Montenegro|PR Montenegro]], Simovi\u0107 moved with his family to [[Kru\u0161evac]], [[People's Republic of Serbia|PR Serbia]] in 1965.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/naslovna/reportaze/aktuelno.293.html:737223-Zoran-Simovic-I-danas-sanjam-da-branim | title=Zoran Simovi\u0107: I danas sanjam da branim | language=Serbian | publisher=novosti.rs | date=9 July 2018 | access-date=28 November 2019}}</ref> He played regularly for [[FK Napredak Kru\u0161evac|Napredak Kru\u0161evac]] during the 1970s, helping them gain promotion to the [[Yugoslav First League]] on two occasions (1975\u201376 and 1977\u201378). In 1980, Simovi\u0107 was transferred to [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]]. He helped the club win the [[Yugoslav Cup]] in the [[1983\u201384 Yugoslav Cup|1983\u201384 season]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://slobodnadalmacija.hr/sport/hajduk/legendarni-vratar-hajduka-nakon-32-godine-ponovno-na-poljudu-322443 | title=Legendarni vratar Hajduka nakon 32 godine ponovno na Poljudu | language=Croatian | publisher=slobodnadalmacija.hr | date=8 August 2016 | access-date=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 1984, Simovi\u0107 moved abroad to Turkey and signed with [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]]. He spent six seasons at the club and won four trophies, including back-to-back national championships ([[1986\u201387 1.Lig|1986\u201387]] and [[1987\u201388 1.Lig|1987\u201388]]). In total, Simovi\u0107 made 192 league appearances and scored once for Galatasaray, converting a penalty kick in a 6\u20130 home win over [[Kahramanmara\u015fspor]] in April 1989.\n\n==International career==\nSimovi\u0107 was capped 10 times for [[Yugoslavia national football team|Yugoslavia]] between 1983 and 1984. He was the team's first-choice goalkeeper at [[UEFA Euro 1984]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.11v11.com/players/zoran-simovic-192206/ | title=Zoran Simovic | publisher=11v11.com | access-date=28 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n;Napredak Kru\u0161evac\n* [[Yugoslav Second League]]: 1975\u201376, 1977\u201378\n;Hajduk Split\n* [[Yugoslav Cup]]: [[1983\u201384 Yugoslav Cup|1983\u201384]]\n;Galatasaray\n* [[S\u00fcper Lig|1.Lig]]: [[1986\u201387 1.Lig|1986\u201387]], [[1987\u201388 1.Lig|1987\u201388]]\n* [[Turkish Cup]]: 1984\u201385\n* [[Turkish Super Cup]]: 1987, 1988\n\n===Individual===\n* [[Yugoslav Footballer of the Year]]: 1983\n* [[Milliyet Sports Awards|Turkish Footballer of the Year]]: 1985, 1986, 1987\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{WorldFootball.net|zoran-simovic}}\n* {{FootballDatabase.eu|32676}}\n* {{NFT player|20075}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 = \n{{Yugoslav Footballer of the Year}}\n{{Turkish Footballer of the Year}}\n}}\n{{Yugoslavia squad UEFA Euro 1984}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Simovic, Zoran}}\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers who have scored]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Turkey]]\n[[Category:FK Napredak Kru\u0161evac players]]\n[[Category:HNK Hajduk Split players]]\n[[Category:Montenegrin footballers]]\n[[Category:People from Mojkovac]]\n[[Category:Serbs of Montenegro]]\n[[Category:S\u00fcper Lig players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 1984 players]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav expatriates in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav First League players]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav footballers]]\n[[Category:Yugoslavia international footballers]]\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Zoran Simovi\u0107\n| image          = \n| fullname       = Zoran Simovi\u0107\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1954|11|02|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Mojkovac]], [[Federal People's Republic of Yugoslavia|FPR Yugoslavia]]\n| he